        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued November 1 at 6:08PM CDT by NWS Houston/Galveston TX</headline>
        <description>At 608 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Markham, or 9 miles west of Bay City, moving southeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Bay City, South Texas Nuclear Plant, Markham, Wadsworth, and
Midfield.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
